  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This assessment evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The intended use scope is defined in the bound regulatory requirement and the claim narrative: prediction of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) across the device operating envelope (flow 2–6 L/min, pressure rise 50–200 mmHg, rotational speed 2000–4000 RPM) to support 510(k) substantial-equivalence demonstration. Full 13-factor assessment performed; 7 factors assessed at or above required level, 6 factors scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-510k",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-piv-velocity-fields",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/material-properties-blood-37c"
  ],
