    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cpb-hemolysis-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The 6 scoped-out factors are appropriately justified under ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for MRL 2. NIH prediction error (14.3% MAPE, 8.2% systematic bias) is within the acceptance threshold for a Class II CPB device 510(k) submission. The computational model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions within the CPB flow and pressure envelope documented in the claim and regulatory requirement. Decision: Accepted.",
